abstract: With a deeper dive into early American history, a gigantic exhibition based on the musical “Hamilton” opens in Chicago.
snippet: With a deeper dive into early American history, a gigantic exhibition based on the musical “Hamilton” opens in Chicago.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Audrey Burcham and Grace Troelstrup got up at 5 a.m. Saturday to be sure they’d make it on time. By 7, three hours before a large “Hamilton” exhibition opened here, they were standing at the front of the line with their moms. Audrey, 12, was clutching an Alexander Hamilton doll as well as a hard-bound collection of inspirational tweets from Lin-Manuel Miranda and, of course, a Playbill; Grace, 13, was wearing a gold star “Hamilton” knit cap and toting “Hamilton: The Revolution,” the explanatory book known to fans as the Hamiltome.

abstract: The couple, both in political-campaign management, met while working on a Senate campaign in 2015, in Colorado.
snippet: The couple, both in political-campaign management, met while working on a Senate campaign in 2015, in Colorado.
lead_paragraph: Jerica Saralaraine Chosich and Andrew Michael Zucker were married April 26. The Rev. Jeffrey L. Maszal, a minister of the United Church of Christ, officiated at Potomac Point Vineyard and Winery in Stafford, Va., with Justin M. Barasky, a friend of the couple, leading the ceremony.

abstract: A trip to the White House from a team based in Charlottesville would have been fraught, regardless of the head coach citing scheduling conflicts.
snippet: A trip to the White House from a team based in Charlottesville would have been fraught, regardless of the head coach citing scheduling conflicts.
lead_paragraph: When the University of Virginia men’s basketball coach, Tony Bennett, announced Friday that his team would decline an invitation to celebrate its N.C.A.A. championship at the White House, he continued a trend of basketball champions’ spurning the traditional fete during the polarizing Trump administration.

abstract: His comments seemed to contradict Facebook’s own estimates that Russian ads and social-media posts reached 126 million Americans during the election.
snippet: His comments seemed to contradict Facebook’s own estimates that Russian ads and social-media posts reached 126 million Americans during the election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Jared Kushner, President Trump’s son-in-law and senior adviser, dismissed Russia’s interference in the 2016 presidential campaign on Tuesday as a “couple of Facebook ads” and said the investigation of it was far more damaging to the country than the intrusion itself.

abstract: Financial ills and a federal investigation, just completed, have led to discord at the club, whose members have included entertainment industry legends.
snippet: Financial ills and a federal investigation, just completed, have led to discord at the club, whose members have included entertainment industry legends.
lead_paragraph: For decades, the Friars Club has been America’s temple of comedy, a fraternity of jokesters and others who relish the rimshot and proudly regard bad taste as a core virtue.

abstract: The cabinet ministers were seen as symbols of progressive feminist government by some, but as backstabbers by others.
snippet: The cabinet ministers were seen as symbols of progressive feminist government by some, but as backstabbers by others.
lead_paragraph: OTTAWA — After promising an open and collaborative way of doing politics, Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada on Tuesday axed from his party two prominent former female cabinet ministers who have been at the center of a festering political crisis about his handling of a criminal case.

abstract: Robert De Niro and Alec Baldwin returned to skewer the Mueller report on “Saturday Night Live,” while Sandra Oh hosted.
snippet: Robert De Niro and Alec Baldwin returned to skewer the Mueller report on “Saturday Night Live,” while Sandra Oh hosted.
lead_paragraph: While the rest of the nation waits to learn if it will ever get to read the final report of the special counsel Robert S. Mueller III, and debates whether a recent letter written by Attorney General William P. Barr provided an adequate overview of the two-year investigation and its results, “Saturday Night Live” is here to tell you what it all means.
